{{single source|date=October 2015}}
[[Lennox Berkeley]] composed his '''Symphony No. 2''' in 1958. The work was commissioned by the [[City of Birmingham Symphony]], who premiered it under [[Andrzej Panufnik]] in February 1959. Berkeley revised the symphony in 1976 for its first recording, by the [[London Philharmonic]] under [[Nicholas Braithwaite]].<ref>{{harvnb|Barnett|2007}}</ref>
==Structure==
The composition is in four movements: # ''[[Tempo#Italian tempo markings|Lento – Allegro]]'' # ''Allegro vivace'' # ''Lento'' # ''Allegro''
Typical playing time is around 27 minutes
