[[File:The Bridge Thornton Dial.jpg|thumb|300px|''The Bridge'' by Thornton Dial]]
'''''The Bridge''''' is a 1997 sculpture by [[Thornton Dial]]. It is located at John Lewis Plaza in [[Freedom Park (Atlanta)|Freedom Park]] in [[Atlanta, Georgia]] at the intersection of [[Ponce de Leon Avenue]] with [[Freedom Parkway]] in the [[Poncey-Highland]] neighborhood.<ref>[http://www.freedompark.org/atlart_ndx_07.html Freedom Park Conservancy website, ''The Bridge'', ''Atlanta Art Park''] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121023001803/http://www.freedompark.org/atlart_ndx_07.html |date=2012-10-23 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.ocaatlanta.com/public_art/the-bridge/ City of Atlanta Office of Cultural Affairs, ''The Bridge'']</ref> The work portrays "congressman [[John Lewis (Georgia politician)|John Lewis]]' lifelong quest for civil and human rights" and the community's "valiant efforts to stop the road and preserve intown neighborhoods".<ref>Plaque at ''The Bridge'' in John Lewis Plaza in Freedom Park</ref>

